<h1><i class="fa fa-search"></i>Searching for Images</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/working-with-images"><i class="fa fa-image"></i>Working with Images</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-search"></i>Searching for Images</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> offers a number of ways to search your images. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>The Search by Photo Menu</h2>
			<p>To view the available options for viewing files and folders, mouse over the Search menu and then over the "By Photo" submenu on your <a href="#help/getting-started/using-desktop">Desktop</a> or a <a href="#apps/file-browser">File Browser</a> app window. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="nested dropdown menu" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-photo-menu@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">The Search by Photo Menu</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-arrows-alt"></i>Search by Resolution</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by either horizontal resolution, vertical resolution, or total pixel count. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-resolution@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Resolution</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-camera"></i>Search by Make/Model</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by the maker or the model of the camera used to capture the photo. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-make-model@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Make/Model</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-arrows-alt-h"></i>Search by Focal Length</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by the focal length of the lens used to capture the image. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-focal-length@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Focal Length</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-dot-circle"></i>Search by Aperture</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by the aperture (F-number) of the lens used to capture the image. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-aperture@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Aperture</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-clock"></i>Search by Exposure</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by the exposure time used to capture the image. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-exposure@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Exposure</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-film"></i>Search by ISO</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by the sensor sensitivity (ISO) used to capture the image. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-iso@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by ISO</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-calendar-alt"></i>Search by Capture Date</h2>
			<p>You can search photos by date that the image was captured. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="search" src="images/help/working-with-images/searching-for-images/search-by-capture-date@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">Search by Capture Date</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>